Festival PHP is a PHP extension designed to offer the basic API of the festival text to speach library described here http://www.cstr.ed.ac.uk/projects/festival/manual/festival_28.html#SEC132

Instalation
----------------------------
Currently will only compile on Ubuntu 10.4 lucid lynx due to some static linking
sudo apt-get install festival festival-dev
cd festival_php
phpize
./confogure --enable-festival_php
make
sudo make install

Usage
----------------------------

php -d extention=festival_php.so -r 'festival_say_text('hello I am PHP');'

php -d extention=festival_php.so -r 'festival_say_file('/etc/motd');'
